## Goal
Find compact TUI patterns (status bar, footer, compact header) as alternatives to `setPinnedHeader()` for orchestration status display.

## Steps
- Step 1: Read @ifi/pi-extension-subagents npm package code tab
- Step 2: Read HazAT/pi-interactive-subagents GitHub repo files
- Step 3: Read pi-tui API docs for setStatus/setFooter/compact header
- Step 4: Read token-saver.ts status widget pattern
- Step 5: Read extensions.md for setStatus/setFooter/notification patterns

Let me start with parallel reads of all available sources.NPM blocked. Using registry API instead. Also need to find pi-tui docs location.Good. Found package info. Let me download source tarball, read GitHub files, and find pi-tui source.Excellent! Found the full ExtensionUIContext API. Now let me check how @ifi subagents and HazAT repo use these APIs.Now I have all the data. Let me verify one more detail about WidgetPlacement options.## Answer

**Best compact alternative:** `setWidget()` with `placement: "aboveEditor"` — NOT `setPinnedHeader()`. Single-line string array, no box overhead, stays above input área, auto-updates.

---

## Evidence

### 1. Full ExtensionUIContext API (all compact alternatives)

From `~/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent/dist/core/extensions/types.d.ts`:

```typescript
/** Placement for extension widgets. */
export type WidgetPlacement = "aboveEditor" | "belowEditor";

export interface ExtensionWidgetOptions {
  /** Where the widget is rendered. Defaults to "aboveEditor". */
  placement?: WidgetPlacement;
}

export interface ExtensionUIContext {
  /** Set status text in the footer/status bar. Pass undefined to clear. */
  setStatus(key: string, text: string | undefined): void;

  /** Set a widget above or below the editor. String[] overload (simplest). */
  setWidget(key: string, content: string[] | undefined, options?: ExtensionWidgetOptions): void;

  /** Set a widget via component factory (full control). */
  setWidget(key: string, content: ((tui: TUI, theme: Theme) => Component & { dispose?(): void }) | undefined, options?: ExtensionWidgetOptions): void;

  /** Custom footer replacement. */
  setFooter(factory: ((tui: TUI, theme: Theme, footerData: ReadonlyFooterDataProvider) => Component & { dispose?(): void }) | undefined): void;

  /** Custom header above chat (not pinned). */
  setHeader(factory: ((tui: TUI, theme: Theme) => Component & { dispose?(): void }) | undefined): void;

  /** Pinned header at top of terminal (takes vertical space from chat). */
  setPinnedHeader(factory: ((tui: TUI, theme: Theme) => Component & { dispose?(): void }) | undefined): void;

  /** Notification toast. */
  notify(message: string, type?: "info" | "warning" | "error"): void;
}
```

### 2. @ifi/pi-extension-subagents — uses `setWidget` with flat string[]

From `/tmp/package/render.ts` (unpacked tarball):

```typescript
// Widget key
export const WIDGET_KEY = "subagent-async";

// Renders compact bullet lines, no box/border
const lines: string[] = [];
lines.push(theme.fg("accent", "Async subagents"));

for (const job of displayedJobs) {
  lines.push(truncLine(
    `- ${id} ${status} | ${agentLabel} | ${stepText}${elapsed ? ` | ${elapsed}` : ""}${tokenText}${activitySuffix}`,
    w,
  ));
}

ctx.ui.setWidget(WIDGET_KEY, lines);  // simple string[] — NO box overhead
```

The @ifi package uses `setWidget` with just `string[]` — no box borders, no padding. The output is flat text lines. This is the **most compact** approach.

### 3. HazAT/pi-interactive-subagents — uses `setWidget` with component factory + border box

From GitHub `pi-extension/subagents/index.ts`:

```typescript
function renderSubagentWidgetLines(agents: RunningSubagent[], width: number): string[] {
  const lines: string[] = [borderTop(title, info, width)];  // ╭─ Title ─ info ─╮
  for (const agent of agents) {
    lines.push(borderLine(left, right, width));              // │ elapsed name   │
  }
  lines.push(borderBottom(width));                           // ╰────────────────╯
  return lines;
}

ctx.ui.setWidget(
  "subagent-status",
  (_tui, _theme) => ({
    invalidate() {},
    render(width: number) {
      return renderSubagentWidgetLines(Array.from(running.values()), width);
    },
  }),
  { placement: "aboveEditor" },  // above input, not consuming chat space
);
```

HazAT uses bordered box (`╭─╮│╰╯`) via component factory. Adds visual grouping but takes 3+ lines overhead (top border + bottom border).

### 4. token-saver.ts — uses `sendMessage` with `customType` (alternative pattern)

From `/Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/token-saver.ts`:

```typescript
pi.on("session_start", async () => {
  if (enabled) {
    pi.sendMessage({
      customType: "token-saver-status",
      content: `[token-saver] Active — ${currentTerseMode} mode`,
      display: true,
    }, { deliverAs: "steer" });
  }
});
```

This sends a custom message into the chat stream. Requires a `MessageRenderer` registration to render differently. Not ideal for persistent orchestration status.

### 5. `setStatus` — most compact (single footer line)

The built-in `FooterComponent` renders a single line at bottom of terminal with: `pwd | model | tokens | ctx% | git-branch | extension-statuses*`.

Extension statuses via `setStatus()` appear appended in this footer line. From `footer-data-provider.d.ts`:

```typescript
export class FooterDataProvider {
  /** Extension status texts set via ctx.ui.setStatus() */
  getExtensionStatuses(): ReadonlyMap<string, string>;
  setExtensionStatus(key: string, text: string | undefined): void;
}
```

**Problem:** `setStatus` values are single-line strings in a crowded footer — can't show multi-step progress.

---

### 6. Comparison Table

| Method | Vertical space | Multi-line? | Auto-update? | Overhead |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `setPinnedHeader(factory)` | Takes from chat scroll | Yes | Via re-render | Full component, 3+ lines |
| `setWidget(key, lines[])` | Above editor only | Yes | Call again with new lines | Zero — flat text |
| `setWidget(key, factory)` | Above editor only | Yes | Re-render on invalidate | Border box ~2 line overhead |
| `setStatus(key, text)` | Footer single line | No | Call again | Minimal |
| `setFooter(factory)` | Footer replacement | Yes | Re-render | Full replacement |
| `sendMessage(customType)` | Chat stream | Yes | New message each update | Chat entry per update |

---

### Recommendation for Orchestrator Plan Panel

**Use `setWidget("orchestrator-status", lines)` with `string[]` content (no box factory).**

Pattern (from @ifi):
```typescript
// Each step change, call:
ctx.ui.setWidget("orchestrator-status", [
  theme.fg("accent", `Plan: step ${current}/${total} | ${elapsed}s`),
  theme.fg("dim", `  → ${currentStepLabel}`),
]);
```

This is the **minimum vertical space** — just your content lines, no box borders, no header padding. Stays above the editor input, does NOT steal scrollable chat area. Widget key deduplication means previous content auto-replaced.

**Set `placement: "belowEditor"` only if you want it below the input line instead.**

